sequenceDiagram
    participant CI as CI Pipeline<br/>(Konflux/Developer)
    participant Extractor as model-extractor<br/>(Go CLI)
    participant HF_API as HuggingFace API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF_Raw as HuggingFace Raw<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant FS as Local Filesystem
    participant Docker as Konflux Build<br/>(Dockerfile.konflux)
    participant Container as Data Container<br/>(ubi9-micro)
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over CI,FS: Flow 1: Model Catalog Generation (Build-Time)
        CI->>Extractor: Execute with --input models-index.yaml
        Extractor->>FS: Read models-index.yaml,<br/>supplemental-catalog.yaml,<br/>vLLM configs, SVG assets
        FS-->>Extractor: Input data

        loop For each model collection
            Extractor->>HF_API: GET /api/collections/{id}<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN (optional)
            HF_API-->>Extractor: Collection metadata (models list)
        end

        loop For each model in collection
            Extractor->>HF_API: GET /api/models/{id}<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN (optional)
            HF_API-->>Extractor: Model details (tags, config)

            Extractor->>HF_Raw: GET /{org}/{model}/raw/main/README.md<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN (optional)
            HF_Raw-->>Extractor: README with YAML frontmatter

            Extractor->>Registry: GET /v2/{repo}/manifests/{tag}
            Registry-->>Extractor: OCI manifest (layers, annotations)

            Extractor->>Registry: GET /v2/{repo}/blobs/{digest}
            Registry-->>Extractor: Container layer (modelcard.md)
        end

        Extractor->>Extractor: Enrich metadata<br/>(priority: HF YAML > modelcard > HF API > tags > defaults)
        Extractor->>FS: Write output/*.yaml (per-model metadata)
        Extractor->>FS: Write data/models-catalog.yaml<br/>data/validated-models-catalog.yaml<br/>data/other-models-catalog.yaml
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over CI,FS: Flow 3: MCP Server Catalog Generation (Build-Time)
        CI->>Extractor: Execute with --mcp-index mcp-servers-index.yaml
        Extractor->>FS: Read input/mcp_servers/*.yaml
        FS-->>Extractor: MCP server definitions

        loop For each MCP server with OCI image
            Extractor->>Registry: GET /v2/{repo}/manifests/{tag}
            Registry-->>Extractor: Architecture + timestamp metadata
        end

        Extractor->>FS: Write data/redhat-mcp-servers-catalog.yaml<br/>data/partner-mcp-servers-catalog.yaml<br/>data/community-mcp-servers-catalog.yaml
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Docker,Dashboard: Flow 2: Data Container Consumption (Runtime)
        Docker->>FS: COPY data/*.yaml /app/data/
        Docker->>Container: Build ubi9-micro image<br/>CMD ["sleep", "infinity"]
        Note over Container: Container runs with<br/>no network, no egress,<br/>UID 1001 (non-root)
        Dashboard->>Container: Volume mount /app/data/
        Container-->>Dashboard: models-catalog.yaml,<br/>MCP server catalogs
    end
